 ','line_number':7,'multiline':True]['text':' Overflow-correctness was proven in bug 1432646 and is explained in the','line_number':52,'multiline':False]['text':' comment below.  This function is very hot, both at compile time and','line_number':53,'multiline':False]['text':' runtime, so disable all overflow checking in it.','line_number':54,'multiline':False]['text':' This algorithm was originally provided here:','line_number':58,'multiline':False]['text':' https://stackoverflow.com/questions/13150449/efficient-unsigned-to-signed-cast-avoiding-implementation-defined-behavior','line_number':59,'multiline':False]['text':'','line_number':60,'multiline':False]['text':' If the value is in the non-negative signed range, just cast.','line_number':61,'multiline':False]['text':'','line_number':62,'multiline':False]['text':' If the value will be negative, compute its delta from the first number','line_number':63,'multiline':False]['text':' past the max signed integer, then add that to the minimum signed value.','line_number':64,'multiline':False]['text':'','line_number':65,'multiline':False]['text':' At the low end: if |u| is the maximum signed value plus one, then it has','line_number':66,'multiline':False]['text':' the same mathematical value as |MinValue| cast to unsigned form.  The','line_number':67,'multiline':False]['text':' delta is zero, so the signed form of |u| is |MinValue| -- exactly the','line_number':68,'multiline':False]['text':' result of adding zero delta to |MinValue|.','line_number':69,'multiline':False]['text':'','line_number':70,'multiline':False]['text':' At the high end: if |u| is the maximum *unsigned* value, then it has all','line_number':71,'multiline':False]['text':' bits set.  |MinValue| cast to unsigned form is purely the high bit set.','line_number':72,'multiline':False]['text':' So the delta is all bits but high set -- exactly |MaxValue|.  And as','line_number':73,'multiline':False]['text':' |MinValue = -MaxValue - 1|, we have |MaxValue + (-MaxValue - 1)| to','line_number':74,'multiline':False]['text':' equal -1.','line_number':75,'multiline':False]['text':'','line_number':76,'multiline':False]['text':' Thus the delta below is in signed range, the corresponding cast is safe,','line_number':77,'multiline':False]['text':' and this computation produces values spanning [MinValue, 0): exactly the','line_number':78,'multiline':False]['text':' desired range of all negative signed integers.','line_number':79,'multiline':False]['text':' namespace detail','line_number':86,'multiline':False]['text':'*
